Provided that the distance metrics in use can be expressed as a combination of linear constraints and
ReLU operators (L1 and L‚àû fall into this category), Œ¥ -local-robustness and (Œ¥ ,Œµ)-global-robustness prop-
erties can be encoded as Reluplex inputs. For the local robustness case, the input constraint ‚Äñ~x‚àí~x0‚Äñ ‚â§ Œ¥
is encoded directly as a set of linear equations and variable bounds, and the robustness property is negated
and encoded as ‚à®
