Encoding (Œ¥ ,Œµ)-global-robustness is more difficult because neither ~x1 nor ~x2 is fixed. It is performed
by encoding two copies of the network, denoted N1 and N2, such that ~x1 is the input to N1 and ~x2 is the
input to N2. We again encode the constraint ‚Äñ~x1‚àí~x2‚Äñ ‚â§ Œ¥ as a set of linear equations, and the robustness
