5.2 Single-Layer Communication
Current deep learning systems [11] allocate noncontiguous mem-
ory for di¬Çerent layers of the neural networks. ¬åey also conduct
multiple rounds of communication for di¬Çerent layers. We allo-
cate the neural networks in a contiguous way and pack all the
layers together and conduct one communication each time. ¬åis
signi¬Äcantly reduces the latency. From Figure 10 we can observe
the bene¬Ät of this technique. ¬åere are two reasons for the im-
provement: (1) ¬åe communication overhead of sending a n-word
message can be formulated as Œ±-Œ≤ model: (Œ± + Œ≤ √ó n) seconds. Œ± is
