For RankSVM, we directly use the implementation in SVMrank [16].
RankBoost, AdaRank, and LambdaMart are implemented using
RankLib2, which is a widely used learning to rank tool.
We refer to our proposed model as ViP. For network con¬Äg-
urations (e.g., numbers of layers and hidden nodes), we tune the
hyper-parameters on a validation set. Speci¬Äcally, in the local per-
ception layer, we set the size of region proposal to 4 √ó 64. We have
also studied the performance of di¬Çerent proposal sizes in Section
4.4. For each proposal, there are 2 convolution layer each followed
by a max pooling layer. In the ¬Ärst convolution layer, there are
8 kernels whose sizes are all set to 2 √ó 2, and the following max
pooling size is 2√ó 2 with strides set to 2. In the Second convolution
layer, there are 16 kernels whose sizes are all set to 2 √ó 2, and the
following max pooling size is the same as the previous max pooling
layer. ¬åus, we get a 1 √ó 16 vector feature for each region proposal.
In the sequential aggregation layer, the dimension of LSTM is set to
10. In the ¬Änal relevance decision layer, the multi-layer perceptron
is a 2-layer feed forward neural network with one hidden layer
whose dimension size is set to 10. ¬åe regularization parameters Œª1
and Œª2 are set to 0.0005 and 0.0001, respectively. All the other train-
able parameters are initialized randomly by uniform distribution
within [‚àí0.1, 0.1].
4.1.4 Evaluation Methodology. Given the limited number of
queries for each collection, we conduct 5-fold cross-validation to
minimize over-¬Ä¬äing without reducing the number of learning
instances. ¬ãeries for each dataset are divided into 5 folds as de-
scribed in LETOR4.0 [26]. ¬åe parameters for each model are tuned
on 4-of-5 folds. ¬åe last fold in each case is used for evaluation.
¬åis process is repeated 5 times once for each fold. ¬åe results
reported were the average over the 5 folds. As for evaluation meas-
ures, precision (P), mean average precision (MAP), and normalized
discounted cumulative gain (NDCG) at position 1, 5, and 10 were
used in our experiments. We performed signi¬Äcant tests using the
paired t-test. Di¬Çerences are considered statistically signi¬Äcant
when the p‚àívalue is lower than 0.05.
